msgstr ""
"Les classes de simulation physique suivantes sont disponibles dans WPILib:"

#: ../../frc-docs/source/docs/software/wpilib-tools/robot-simulation/physics-sim.rst:21
msgid "LinearSystemSim, for modeling systems with linear dynamics"
msgstr ""
"LinearSystemSim, pour la modﾃｩlisation de systﾃｨmes avec dynamique linﾃｩaire"

#: ../../frc-docs/source/docs/software/wpilib-tools/robot-simulation/physics-sim.rst:22
msgid "FlywheelSim"
msgstr "Volant d'inertie"

#: ../../frc-docs/source/docs/software/wpilib-tools/robot-simulation/physics-sim.rst:23
msgid "DifferentialDrivetrainSim"
msgstr "DiffﾃｩrentielDrivetrainSim"

#: ../../frc-docs/source/docs/software/wpilib-tools/robot-simulation/physics-sim.rst:26
msgid ""
"BatterySim, which simply estimates battery voltage sag based on drawn "
"currents"
msgstr ""
"BatterySim, qui estime simplement l'affaissement de la tension de la "
"batterie en fonction des courants tirﾃｩs"

#: ../../frc-docs/source/docs/software/wpilib-tools/robot-simulation/physics-sim.rst:28
msgid ""
"All simulation classes (with the exception of the differential drive "
"simulator) inherit from the :code:`LinearSystemSim` class. By default, the "
"dynamics are the linear system dynamics :math:`\\mathbf{x}_{k+1} = "
"\\mathbf{A}\\mathbf{x}_k + \\mathbf{B}\\mathbf{u}_k`. Subclasses override "
"the :code:`UpdateX(x, u, dt)` method to provide custom, nonlinear dynamics, "
"such as modeling gravity."
msgstr ""
"Toutes les classes de simulation (ﾃ l'exception du simulateur d'entraﾃｮnement"
" diffﾃｩrentiel) hﾃｩritent de la classe :code:`LinearSystemSim`. Par dﾃｩfaut, la"
" dynamique est la dynamique du systﾃｨme linﾃｩaire :math:`\\mathbf{x}_{k+1} = "
"\\mathbf{A}\\mathbf{x}_k + \\mathbf{B}\\mathbf{u}_k`. Les sous-classes "
"remplacent la mﾃｩthode :code:`UpdateX(x, u, dt)` pour fournir une dynamique "
"non linﾃｩaire personnalisﾃｩe, comme la modﾃｩlisation de la gravitﾃｩ."

#: ../../frc-docs/source/docs/software/wpilib-tools/robot-simulation/physics-sim.rst:33
msgid "Usage in User Code"
msgstr "Utilisation dans le code utilisateur"

#: ../../frc-docs/source/docs/software/wpilib-tools/robot-simulation/physics-sim.rst:41
msgid ""
"The elevator and arm simulators will prevent the simulated position from "
"exceeding given minimum or maximum heights or angles. If you wish to "
"simulate a mechanism with infinite rotation or motion, "
":code:`LinearSystemSim` may be a better option."
msgstr ""
"Les simulateurs d'ﾃｩlﾃｩvateur et de bras empﾃｪcheront la position simulﾃｩe de "
"dﾃｩpasser des hauteurs ou des angles minimum ou maximum donnﾃｩs. Si vous "
"souhaitez simuler un mﾃｩcanisme avec une rotation ou un mouvement infini, "
":code:`LinearSystemSim` peut ﾃｪtre une meilleure option."

#: ../../frc-docs/source/docs/software/wpilib-tools/robot-simulation/physics-sim.rst:0
msgid "Java"
msgstr "Java"

#: ../../frc-docs/source/docs/software/wpilib-tools/robot-simulation/physics-sim.rst:0
msgid "C++"
msgstr "C++"

#: ../../frc-docs/source/docs/software/wpilib-tools/robot-simulation/physics-sim.rst:61
msgid ""
"Next, :code:`teleopPeriodic`/:code:`TeleopPeriodic` (Java/C++) uses a simple"
" PID control loop to drive our elevator to a setpoint 30 inches off the "
"ground."
msgstr ""
"Ensuite, :code:`teleopPeriodic`/:code:`TeleopPeriodic` (Java/C++) utilise "
"une simple boucle de contrﾃｴle PID pour conduire notre elevateur ﾃ un point "
"de consigne ﾃ 30 pouces (76 cm) du sol."

#: ../../frc-docs/source/docs/software/wpilib-tools/robot-simulation/physics-sim.rst:91
msgid ""
"Next, :code:`simulationPeriodic`/:code:`SimulationPeriodic` (Java/C++) uses "
"the voltage applied to the motor to update the simulated position of the "
"elevator. We use :code:`SimulationPeriodic` because it runs periodically "
"only for simulated robots. This means that our simulation code will not be "
"run on a real robot."
msgstr ""
"Puis, :code:`simulationPeriodic`/:code:`SimulationPeriodic` (Java/C++) "
"utilise la tension appliquﾃｩe au moteur pour mettre ﾃ jour la position "
"simulﾃｩe de l'ﾃｩlﾃｩvateur. Nous utilisons :code:`SimulationPeriodic` car il "
"s'exﾃｩcute seulement que pour les robots simulﾃｩs. Cela signifie que notre "
"code de simulation ne sera pas exﾃｩcutﾃｩ sur un vrai robot."

#: ../../frc-docs/source/docs/software/wpilib-tools/robot-simulation/physics-sim.rst:95
msgid ""
"Finally, the simulated encoder's distance reading is set using the simulated"
" elevator's position, and the robot's battery voltage is set using the "
"estimated current drawn by the elevator."
msgstr ""
"Enfin, la lecture de la distance du codeur simulﾃｩ est rﾃｩglﾃｩe en utilisant la"
" position simulﾃｩe de l'ﾃｩlﾃｩvateur, et la tension de la batterie du robot est "
"rﾃｩglﾃｩe en utilisant le courant estimﾃｩ tirﾃｩ par l'ascenseur."
